Based on recent studies, it is shown that a large number of stable or sub-stable 2D structures can be formed using Ti and B [101–104]. Different from MAB structures with orthorhombic symmetry, Ti2InB2 displays hexagonal P6¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
